[Deal "E:KQ753.87.KQ6.Q95 42.KJ94.T95.T863 AJ8.Q652.873.A74 T96.AT3.AJ42.KJ2"]
[BoardVersionToken "40cdd9d9acb396fd92851d9c3e75fe57c9bcf38e59cf8288334bd685374ebaaf"]
[Student "S"]
[Category "Bidding Conventions"]
[Difficulty "intermediate"]
[SkillPath "bidding_conventions/two_over_one"]
[Auction "E"]
1S Pass 1NT Pass 2C Pass 3S Pass Pass Pass
{How do you start the bidding on this hand? 
You open 1\s.  Partner responds 1NT, forcing for one round.  What do you rebid? 
You rebid 2\C, a 3-card suit. West now jumps to 3\S, showing limit-raise strength. This sequence is the way to show a limit-raise with only 3 trumps; an immediate jump-raise to the 3-level shows a limit-raise with 4 trumps.

In any case you have a bare minimum and pass the invitation.
}

